    <section id="wowFeed">
        <h2 class="h2">World of Warcraft RSS Feed</h2>
        <figure class="figure--icon">
            {{> link-logo url='https://www.worldofwarcraft.com/' icon='wow'}}
        </figure>
        <p>Since their last redesign Blizzard doesnâ€™t provide an RSS feed on their armory-website anymore. They do
            however
            offer an API to access a JSON-encoded activity feed for character and guilds. Since a colleague held a
            presentation about node.js and how easy it is to deploy a server-app with it, I took the opportunity to
            enhance my javascript knowledge and wrote this JSON-to-RSS-Feed Converter for World-Of-Warcraft:</p>

        <form class="form" action="https://wowfeed.herokuapp.com">

            {{> input-text
                name='character'
                id='charname'
                label='Character'}}

            {{> input-text
                name='realm'
                id='charrealm'
                label='Realm'}}

            <span class="input__block input__select">
                <select id="char_region" name="region" class="select">
                    <option value="-1" selected>Region</option>
                    <option value="eu">Europe</option>
                    <option value="us">US</option>
                    <option value="tw">Taiwan</option>
                    <option value="kr">Korea</option>
                </select>
            </span>

            <button class="btn btn--md" type="submit">Get RSS</button>
        </form>

        <form class="form" action="https://wowfeed.herokuapp.com">

            {{> input-text
                name='guild'
                id='guildname'
                label='Guild'}}

            {{> input-text
                name='realm'
                id='guildrealm'
                label='Realm'}}

            <span class="input__block input__select">
                <select id="guild_region" name="region" class="select">
                    <option value="-1" selected>Region</option>
                    <option value="eu">Europe</option>
                    <option value="us">US</option>
                    <option value="tw">Taiwan</option>
                    <option value="kr">Korea</option>
                </select>
            </span>

            <button class="btn btn--md" type="submit">Get RSS</button>
        </form>
    </section>

